Singapore's issue is our people are stuck with the notion of our own flavor of "zero-COVID". Our measures at the start were so stringent that cases were kept so low, and people expect it to continue to be low despite virus mutations and global shifts. We know more now than then.

The fastest way to reduce the load A&E and healthcare is facing is to treat COVID like a flu. We know 99.7% have no or mild symptoms (MOH statistic). The extra precautions are creating extreme stress on the system.

Straits Times, Nov 6 2021, [Singapore's overall death rate did not increase despite Covid-19]: "Singapore's overall death rate has not increased despite more deaths from Covid-19, ... because those who died from the virus would likely have otherwise perished from other

Keep in mind that people who die WITH COVID is inevitable as the virus makes its way around. Comorbidities is another factor. At this point, there's much to be said about the impact of COVID on both physical and mental health, and how it's more damaging than COVID itself.
